<div id="banner">
	<h1>&#8220;Essential Blogging&#8221; for Review</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Nat has put <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/cs/weblog/view/wlg/1440">zipped PDFs of &#8220;Essential Blogging&#8221;</a>, O&#8217;Reilly&#8217;s new blogging book up on the Web. Is it just me, or are zipped PDFs the new way to distribute things you don&#8217;t really want distributed?</p>

<p>&lt;sbp> argh, postscript is better than any other encryption algorithm known to man</p>

<p>Also, they&#8217;re looking for <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/~rael/2002/May/22#blogging_voices_request">input from bloggers</a> to put in the final chapter of the book.</p>

